cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with transcription of spontaneous speech and disfluencies, which are related to natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech and its transcription. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of transcription errors on evaluation of automatic disfluency detection, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with automatic detection of disfluencies, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper sheds light on human perception of disfluencies and other conversational speech phenomena, which is relevant to HCI.
